SUMMARY:Sleeping Beauty Ballet of Lights in a Sparkling Show (Front St)
DESCRIPTION:Experience Toronto\nNote: Seats became available this morning 
 and will sell out\, so purchase your ticket asap.\n\nOn **Saturday March 2
 8th\,** **see the new Ballet of Lights Sleeping Beauty in a Sparkling Show
 .** This beloved tale is brought to life through classical dance\, stunnin
 g choreography and beautiful glow-in-dark costumes. Six incredible local d
 ancers light up the stage in costumes that transform every moment in a rad
 iant display. I am seated in Zone C. **Purchase: Ballet of Lights Sleeping
  Beauty in a Sparkling Show on Saturday March 28th at 6pm (be careful as t
 here are other dates and time slots on the same day).**\n\n**COST**\nRegul
 ar: Adults $30 - 84 + taxes + fees\n\nMeetup Organizer Fee: $5\n\n**Ticket
  Policy**: All sales are final\, no refunds or exchanges.\n\n**SIGNING-UP*
 *\n\n* **RSVP Yes** **(everyone goes on the waitlist until they post they 
 purchased their tickets)**\n* **[Purchase](https://feverup.com/m/396867?ut
 m_source=fever_app_share&utm_medium=plan_detail&utm_campaign=396867_yyz&re
 f=ISABELM84996)**[ ](https://tickets.mirvish.com/tina/20416)your own ticke
 t by selecting Tickets\, March 28th\, 6pm (caution there are multiple date
 s and times)\n\nA reminder will be sent the day before with my cell and re
 minder details where to meet and when.\n\nRSVPs close 1 day prior and the 
 Waitlist will be removed at that time. Cancellations will result in a No S
 how and impact future attendance.\n\n**MEETUP TIME**\n**Meet me at: 5:40pm
 ** **inside the front doors of Young People's Theatre at 165 Front St. E**
 \n\n**Show Starts: 6pm (there is no late entry)**\n\nLength: 60 mins\n\nAf
 ter: I'll drive us to dinner at a restaurant nearby\n\nEnjoy and please po
 st your comments in the Event after.
